Reference-contexts: We have extended the system by semantically categorizing descriptions using WordNet <ref> (Miller et al., 1990) </ref>, so that a generator can more easily determine which description is relevant in different contexts. PROFILE can also be used in a real-time fashion to monitor entities and the changes of descriptions associated with them over the course of time. <p> Like this research, our work also aims at extracting proper nouns without the aid of large word lists. We use a regular grammar encoding part-of-speech categories to extract certain text patterns and we use WordNet <ref> (Miller et al., 1990) </ref> to provide semantic filtering. Our work on extracting descriptions is quite similar to the work carried out under the DARPA message understanding program for extracting descriptions (MUC, 1992). <p> Counts for three-word noun phrases are shown in the right-hand column. We show counts for multiple and unique occurrences of the same noun phrase. * Weeding out of false candidates. Our system analyzed all candidates for entity names using WordNet <ref> (Miller et al., 1990) </ref> and removed from consideration those that contain words appearing in WordNet's dictionary. This resulted in a list of 421 unique entity names that we used for the automatic description extraction stage.
